start-details:

h2:Bash Operator

This node executes a Bash script, command or set of commands.

end-details:

start-examples:

h2: Bash Operator Examples

h4: Example of a Simple Bash Command

Command: echo 'Hello, World!'

This command prints "Hello, World!" to the console.

h4: Example of Executing a Script

Command: bash my_script.sh

This command runs a Bash script named my_script.sh. Ensure that the script has execute permissions.

h4: Example of Setting Environment Variables

Command:
export MY_VAR='Hello';
echo $MY_VAR

This command sets an environment variable MY_VAR and then echoes its value.

h4: Example of Using Conditional Logic

if [ -f /path/to/file ]; then
echo 'File exists';
else
echo 'File does not exist';
fi

This command checks if a specific file exists and echoes the appropriate message.

h4: Usage

* Task ID: "bash_operator_task"
* Trigger Rule: all_success
* Shell Command: echo 'Hello, World!'

end-examples: